#. type: Title ==
#: ../src/redstone-link.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Operating Principle"
msgstr ""

#. type: #principle
#: ../src/redstone-link.adoc:25
msgid "A redstone link has 2 modes of operation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: horizontal
#: ../src/redstone-link.adoc:28
msgid ""
"Sends the powered state of its incoming redstone connections to other "
"redstone links on the same channel."
msgstr ""

#. type: horizontal
#: ../src/redstone-link.adoc:29
msgid ""
"Receives from other redstone links on the same channel. If any of them is "
"powered, it powers its outgoing redstone connections."
msgstr ""

#. type: horizontal
#: ../src/redstone-link.adoc:31
msgid ""
"Redstone links are distinguished by channels, which consists of 2 item "
"types. Each channel carries a redstone signal independently of the others. "
"Examples of distinct channels are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: horizontal
#: ../src/redstone-link.adoc:33
msgid "(Oak Plank, Cobblestone)"
msgstr ""

#. type: horizontal
#: ../src/redstone-link.adoc:34
msgid "(Oak Plank, Air)"
msgstr ""

#. type: horizontal
#: ../src/redstone-link.adoc:35
msgid "(Air, Oak Plank)"
msgstr ""

#. type: horizontal
#: ../src/redstone-link.adoc:36
msgid "(Air, Air)"
msgstr ""

#. type: #configuration
#: ../src/redstone-link.adoc:41
msgid ""
"After placing a redstone link on the virtual board, clicking the component "
"opens its configuration screen."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: ../src/redstone-link.adoc:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "Redstone link settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: #configuration
#: ../src/redstone-link.adoc:54
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"❶ ❷ Channel::\n"
"  Place an item, or drag a ghost item from JEI, to set the channel of the redstone link.\n"
"❸ Relocate button::\n"
"  Click to move the location of this redstone link on the virtual board.\n"
"❹ Add connection button::\n"
"  Click to connect to other components via redstone. Directions of connections are decided automatically. Send-mode links may only have incoming connections, receive-mode links may only have outgoing connections.\n"
"❺ Mode switch::\n"
"  Click to switch between send image:btn-send-mode.png[,18,18] and receive image:btn-receive-mode.png[,18,18] modes.\n"
"❻ Confirm button::\n"
"  Click to confirm settings and close the screen.\n"
msgstr ""
